            <title>[JDK-8274400] HotSpot Style Guide should permit use of alignof</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8274400</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The alignof operator was added by C++11.  It returns the alignment for the given type.  Various metaprogramming usages exist, in particular when using std::aligned_storage.  Use of this operator should be permitted in HotSpot code.</description>
